<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 93 / Letter: Suppliers offer as much real value as customers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr RICHARD GREENSTED
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Although Messrs Furnham and Pendleton (Management: 'Seduced by the
customer cult', June 7) make some intelligent remarks about the customer
cult, they appear to have forgotten one important company stakeholder, the
supplier. Suppliers invest considerable resources in the continuing good
fortune of their clients, but are rarely treated as key contributors to a
company's success. Exceptions such as British Airways, Marks and Spencer and
the Royal Bank of Scotland are as scarce as they are enlightened.
Suppliers treated as stakeholders will quickly become partners and will add
real value to a company's bottom line.
Richard Greensted,
Richard Greensted Associates,
9 Burghley Avenue,
New Malden, Surrey KT3 4SW
</TEXT>
<XX>
