FT  11 JUN 93 / World Trade News: Corning sells optical fibre to Russians
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CORNING, the US speciality glass and materials company, yesterday announced
a long-term agreement to supply optical fibre to Russia for use in its
planned civilian telephone network, writes Andrew Fisher.
The All Russian Scientific Institute of the Cable Industry and four Russian
cable manufacturers will buy the optical fibre for use in making fibre optic
cable. They will also consider manufacturing optical fibre using Corning's
technology.
Mr Izyaslav Peshkov, director of the institute, said Russia planned to build
a telecommunications network compatible with those in western Europe.
