<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Delyn shares rise on 90% advance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Delyn Group rose 16 per cent to 77p yesterday as the paper,
packaging and printing group announced a 90 per cent jump in pre-tax profits
for the year to January 31.
On turnover of Pounds 12.3m (Pounds 13.1m), the pre-tax result of Pounds
998,000 (Pounds 524,000) was achieved after an exceptional charge of Pounds
59,000 (Pounds 42,000).
Earnings rose to 7.31p (3.32p) per share and the proposed final dividend is
increased to 1.17p for a 1.67p (1.45p) total.
Mr Paul Norman, chairman, said the board had considered various options to
develop the company and it intended to expand into the housing market.
