<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 93 / Observer: Well staged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dramatic emphasis was given to the much improved results presented by Chubb
Security's Sir Ernest Harrison, whose policy of demerging Vodafone and Chubb
from Racal has staved off hostile bids, and seen the value of all three
companies rise.
He gave his presentation at London's Waldorf hotel. Playing at the theatre
next door . . . The Importance of Being Earnest.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Chubb Security Installations.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
