FT  11 JUN 93 / Ford plant rivals Japanese output
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FORD'S ENGINES plant at Bridgend in south Wales is achieving greater
productivity than rival Japanese car manufacturers, Mr Ray Pittman, European
engine operations manager, said yesterday.
He made the claim as Ford disclosed that pan-European demand for its new
Mondeo family car range had led to Bridgend almost doubling production of
Zeta engines.
Mr Pittman said Bridgend was capable of building 100 units an hour.
Comparable Japanese plants were building equivalent 16-valve engines at 60
to 70 units an hour.
