FT  11 JUN 93 / Working change delayed by BT
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PLAN by British Telecommunications to fit working patterns to customer
needs - including more weekend working and daily cover from 6am to 10pm for
engineers - faces resistance from the National Communications Union, the
main BT union, David Goodhart writes.
The NCU's annual conference yesterday voted to back a strike ballot if
compulsory weekend working or flexible starting and finishing times are
imposed by BT.
BT had originally planned to implement its flexible working proposals - the
Customer Service Improvement Programme - in October but has agreed to defer
it until April.
