<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Euro-seat bill published today
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FIVE OF the UK's six extra constituencies for the European parliament -
agreed at the Edinburgh summit - will go to England, and the remaining one
will go to Wales under the arrangements set out in a government bill to be
published today.
The legislation must be passed by October, in order for the new boundaries
to be set in time for the Euro-elections next summer. But the plans are
certain to attract vocal, and perhaps prolonged, opposition because there
will be no extra seat for Scotland.
The bill is scheduled to face all its Commons' stages on Monday.
