<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / The Lex Column: Skandia
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The sale of Uni Storebrand's and Hafnia's stakes in Skandia is almost the
end of the sorry Nordic saga. With Skandia's share register free of
unwelcome influences, and Hafnia in the hands of Sun Alliance, all that
remains is to repair Uni Storebrand's balance sheet. Since Uni bought its
shares at an average price of Skr220 and has sold at less than half that, it
is easy to see how the damage was done. The Norwegian institutions now being
asked to plug the gap must keep a tight rein on the imperial ambitions of
the company's management. All in all the episode is a reminder of just why
continental European insurers trade at a discount to net assets.
</TEXT>
