<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 93 / International Company News: Fed approves Bank of Boston
acquisitions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAMIAN FRASER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BANK of Boston, the largest bank in Massachusetts, has been given approval
by the US Federal Reserve to buy two New England banks, Multibank Financial
and Society for Savings Bancorp.
The Bank of Boston will pay with its own shares an equivalent of around
Dollars 232m for Multibank, and Dollars 215m for Society for Savings. The
two banks would add Dollars 4.8bn to Bank of Boston's existing assets of
Dollars 32bn.
The purchase is still conditional on approval by the Massachusetts Board of
Bank Incorporation, but this is expected to be a formality. Bank of Boston
had to promise to raise around Dollars 170m in new capital to win approval
from the Federal Reserve for the purchase of Multibank.
Two Federal Board governors opposed the authorisation, on the grounds that
the promise to raise new capital was not part of the Bank of Boston's
original application. The two members believed the addition of new
information after the original application 'impairs the integrity of the
Board's decision-making process'.
</TEXT>
